      • processRawResultsNoMeta

        protected WCResultSet[] processRawResultsNoMeta(WCConnection connection,
                                    WCStatement statement,
                                    java.lang.String query,
                                    java.lang.String rawResult)
                                         throws java.sql.SQLException
        For empty results (other than those in a batch) return an empty resultset. No resultset-metadata is returned from this method.
        Parameters:
        connection - WCConnection - parent connection.
        statement - WCStatement - related to this rawResult.
        query - String - the query/ies related to this rawResult.
        rawResult - String - containing .csv-ish data. First row contains column names.
        Returns:
        a WCResultSet[] containing all resultsets from the processed data.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - - if something goes wrong.

      • processRawResults

        protected WCResultSet[] processRawResults(WCConnection connection,
                              WCStatement statement,
                              java.lang.String query,
                              java.lang.String rawResult)
                                   throws java.sql.SQLException
        For empty results (other than those in a batch) return an empty resultset. Where possible basic resultset-metadata is returned with each resultset.
        Parameters:
        connection - WCConnection - parent connection.
        statement - WCStatement - related to this rawResult.
        query - String - the query/ies related to this rawResult.
        rawResult - String - containing .csv-ish data. First row contains column names.
        Returns:
        a WCResultSet[] containing all resultsets from the processed data.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - - if something goes wrong.
